---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Navbar from '../../components/Navbar.astro';
import ContactForm from '../../components/ContactForm.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
import ParallaxBanner from '../../components/ParallaxBanner.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="The Home Buying Process | Buyer's Guide | Cody Posey Real Estate"
  description="A step-by-step guide to buying a home in New Braunfels, TX — from finding a REALTOR to closing day."
>
  <Navbar />
  <main style="padding-top: 80px;">

    <!-- Hero -->
    <div class="sub-hero">
      <div class="sub-hero__overlay"></div>
      <div class="sub-hero__content">
        <nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
          <a href="/">Home</a> <span>/</span> <a href="/buyers-guide">Buyer's Guide</a> <span>/</span> <span>Home Buying Process</span>
        </nav>
        <h1>The Home Buying <span style="color:#FF1616;">Process</span></h1>
        <p>A step-by-step overview from start to keys in hand</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Steps -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <p class="page-intro">Buying a home can feel overwhelming, but it doesn't have to be. Here's a clear breakdown of what to expect at each stage of the process. Having a trusted REALTOR&reg; by your side makes every step smoother.</p>

        <div class="process-overview">
          <p>The average home purchase in Texas takes about 30 to 45 days from accepted offer to closing, but the timeline can vary depending on the type of financing, the results of inspections, and how quickly both parties respond to requests. Starting your preparation early — particularly getting pre-approved and finding the right agent — can shave weeks off the process and reduce stress significantly.</p>
          <p>In the New Braunfels market, homes in desirable neighborhoods often receive offers within the first week of listing. Being prepared with your financing and having a clear understanding of the steps below means you can move quickly when the right home comes along. Here is a detailed look at each phase of the journey from first conversation to moving day.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="steps">
          <div class="step">
            <div class="step__number">1</div>
            <div class="step__content">
              <h3>Find a REALTOR&reg; You Can Trust</h3>
              <p>There's no commitment required on your part for the initial meeting. It will be educational and help you identify your next steps. A good agent will guide you through the entire process and advocate for your best interests. Look for someone with local market knowledge, strong communication skills, and a track record you can verify through reviews and references. In a competitive market like New Braunfels, having an agent who knows the neighborhoods, the builders, and the inventory can give you a real edge.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="step">
            <div class="step__number">2</div>
            <div class="step__content">
              <h3>Obtain Financial Pre-Qualification</h3>
              <p>Your real estate agent will assist you in the pre-qualification process by connecting you with lenders and guiding you through the necessary documents. This step clarifies your budget and strengthens your offer. A pre-approval letter shows sellers that a lender has reviewed your income, credit, and assets and is willing to fund your purchase up to a specific amount. In a market where multiple offers are common, a strong pre-approval can be the factor that gets your offer accepted over a competing one.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="step">
            <div class="step__number">3</div>
            <div class="step__content">
              <h3>Select &amp; View Properties</h3>
              <p>Begin touring homes in your price range and desired location. Narrow down your preferences, such as size, style, and neighborhood. Your agent will set up a customized search based on your criteria. Think beyond the house itself — consider commute times, school zones, HOA rules, flood zones, and future development plans. In New Braunfels, your experience can vary widely depending on whether you are looking at established neighborhoods near downtown, new construction communities along the 46 corridor, or acreage properties in the surrounding Hill Country.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="step">
            <div class="step__number">4</div>
            <div class="step__content">
              <h3>Make an Offer</h3>
              <p>Once you find a home you like, work with your agent to submit a competitive offer with terms and price. You may include earnest money, an option fee, and an option for the right to back out during the inspection period. The seller may accept, counter, or reject your offer. Your agent will help you craft an offer that balances competitiveness with protecting your interests. This includes determining the right price based on comparable sales, choosing an appropriate option period length, and deciding whether to request seller concessions toward closing costs.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="step">
            <div class="step__number">5</div>
            <div class="step__content">
              <h3>Accept the Contract</h3>
              <p>After your offer is accepted, review the terms and conditions carefully. Work with your agent or attorney to ensure you're comfortable before signing. Complete inspections and remove contingencies during the option period. The option period is your safety net — during this time, you can have the home professionally inspected for structural issues, electrical problems, plumbing concerns, roof condition, and more. If major issues are found, you can negotiate repairs, request a price reduction, or walk away entirely.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="step">
            <div class="step__number">6</div>
            <div class="step__content">
              <h3>Complete Mortgage Application</h3>
              <p>Submit your full mortgage application to the lender, providing all required financial documents. This finalizes your loan approval and locks in your interest rate. The lender will order a credit report, appraisal, and verifications. During this stage, avoid making any major financial changes — do not open new credit cards, take out loans, make large purchases, or change jobs. Any of these actions can jeopardize your loan approval, even if you were already pre-approved. Stay in close communication with your lender and respond to document requests promptly.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="step">
            <div class="step__number">7</div>
            <div class="step__content">
              <h3>Final Details</h3>
              <p>Complete paperwork, sign final loan documents, do a final walk-through, and confirm closing arrangements before receiving your keys. Contact the title company to coordinate the closing. The final walk-through is your opportunity to verify that any agreed-upon repairs were completed, that the home is in the same condition as when you made your offer, and that all fixtures and appliances included in the contract are still present. This typically happens the day before or the morning of closing.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="step">
            <div class="step__number">8</div>
            <div class="step__content">
              <h3>Closing Day</h3>
              <p>This is the transfer of funds and ownership. Sign the final paperwork, pay closing costs, and receive the keys to your new home. Closing typically takes place at the title company's office in New Braunfels. Plan to spend about an hour signing documents. You will need to bring a government-issued photo ID and a cashier's check or wire transfer for your closing costs and down payment. Once everything is signed and funds are disbursed, you will receive the keys to your new home.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CTA -->
    <section class="sub-cta">
      <div class="sub-cta__overlay"></div>
      <div class="container" style="position: relative; z-index: 1;">
        <h2>Ready to Get <span class="accent">Started</span>?</h2>
        <p style="color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7); max-width: 600px; margin: 1rem auto 2rem;">I'll walk you through every step and make sure you feel confident from start to finish.</p>
        <div style="display: flex; gap: 1rem; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap;">
          <a href="#contact" class="btn btn-primary">Let's Connect</a>
          <a href="/buyers-guide" class="btn btn-outline">Back to Buyer's Guide</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- FAQ Section -->
    <section class="faq-section">
      <div class="container">
        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions About the Home Buying Process</h2>
        <div class="faq-list">
          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>How long does it take to buy a home in New Braunfels?</summary>
            <p>From the time your offer is accepted to closing day, most transactions take between 30 and 45 days. However, the total timeline depends on factors like your loan type, how quickly inspections and appraisals are scheduled, and whether any issues arise during the process. If you are pre-approved and ready to move quickly, you can start touring homes and submitting offers right away. The preparation stage — getting pre-approved and finding the right agent — can take an additional one to two weeks depending on your financial situation.</p>
          </details>
          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>What is the option period and why is it important for buyers in Texas?</summary>
            <p>The option period is a negotiated timeframe, typically 7 to 10 days, during which you have the unrestricted right to terminate the contract for any reason. In exchange, you pay a small option fee to the seller. This period is critical because it gives you time to have the home professionally inspected and to uncover any issues before you are fully committed. If the inspection reveals problems, you can negotiate repairs, ask for a price reduction, or walk away. The option period is one of the strongest buyer protections in the Texas real estate process.</p>
          </details>
          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>What should I avoid doing after I get pre-approved for a mortgage?</summary>
            <p>Once you are pre-approved, your lender has evaluated your financial profile at a specific point in time. Any changes to your finances can put your approval at risk. Avoid opening new credit accounts, making large purchases on credit, co-signing loans for others, changing jobs, or moving large sums of money between accounts without documenting the source. Even small changes can trigger additional underwriting reviews that delay your closing or cause your loan to be denied. Stay in close contact with your lender and ask before making any financial moves.</p>
          </details>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

  </main>
  <ParallaxBanner image="/images/generated/guadalupe-river.png" />

  <script type="application/ld+json">
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How long does it take to buy a home in New Braunfels?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "From the time your offer is accepted to closing day, most transactions take between 30 and 45 days. However, the total timeline depends on factors like your loan type, how quickly inspections and appraisals are scheduled, and whether any issues arise during the process. If you are pre-approved and ready to move quickly, you can start touring homes and submitting offers right away. The preparation stage — getting pre-approved and finding the right agent — can take an additional one to two weeks depending on your financial situation."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is the option period and why is it important for buyers in Texas?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "The option period is a negotiated timeframe, typically 7 to 10 days, during which you have the unrestricted right to terminate the contract for any reason. In exchange, you pay a small option fee to the seller. This period is critical because it gives you time to have the home professionally inspected and to uncover any issues before you are fully committed. If the inspection reveals problems, you can negotiate repairs, ask for a price reduction, or walk away. The option period is one of the strongest buyer protections in the Texas real estate process."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What should I avoid doing after I get pre-approved for a mortgage?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Once you are pre-approved, your lender has evaluated your financial profile at a specific point in time. Any changes to your finances can put your approval at risk. Avoid opening new credit accounts, making large purchases on credit, co-signing loans for others, changing jobs, or moving large sums of money between accounts without documenting the source. Even small changes can trigger additional underwriting reviews that delay your closing or cause your loan to be denied. Stay in close contact with your lender and ask before making any financial moves."
        }
      }
    ]
  }
  </script>

  <ContactForm context="I'm ready to start the home buying process..." />
  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  .sub-hero {
    position: relative;
    height: 280px;
    background: url('/images/generated/home-nb-twostory.png') center/cover no-repeat;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    text-align: center;
    color: #fff;
  }

  .sub-hero__overlay {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background: rgba(0,0,0,0.55);
  }

  .sub-hero__content {
    position: relative;
    z-index: 1;
    padding: 0 1.5rem;
  }

  .sub-hero__content h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3.2rem);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .sub-hero__content p {
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  .breadcrumb {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5);
  }

  .breadcrumb a {
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5);
    transition: color 0.2s;
  }

  .breadcrumb a:hover { color: #FF1616; }
  .breadcrumb span { margin: 0 0.3rem; }

  .page-intro {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    color: var(--gray);
    line-height: 1.8;
    max-width: 800px;
    text-align: center;
    margin: 0 auto 3rem;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .steps {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .step {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    align-items: flex-start;
    padding: 1.5rem 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(0,0,0,0.08);
  }

  .step:last-child { border-bottom: none; }

  .step__number {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    width: 48px;
    height: 48px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: #FF1616;
    color: #fff;
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
  }

  .step__content h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: 1rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
  }

  .step__content p {
    color: var(--gray);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .sub-cta {
    position: relative;
    padding: 5rem 0;
    color: #fff;
    text-align: center;
    background-image: url('/images/testimonials-hero.jpg');
    background-size: cover;
    background-position: center;
    background-attachment: fixed;
    background-color: #333;
  }

  .sub-cta__overlay {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background: rgba(0,0,0,0.65);
  }

  .sub-cta h2 { color: #fff; }

  .process-overview {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto 2rem;
  }

  .process-overview p {
    color: var(--gray);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  /* FAQ */
  .faq-section { padding: 4rem 0; background: #f9f9f9; }
  .faq-section h2 { text-align: center; margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  .faq-list { max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .faq-item { background: #fff; border: 1px solid #eee; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .faq-item summary { padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem; font-weight: 600; cursor: pointer; font-size: 1rem; list-style: none; display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; }
  .faq-item summary::after { content: '+'; font-size: 1.3rem; color: #FF1616; font-weight: 700; }
  .faq-item[open] summary::after { content: '\2212'; }
  .faq-item p { padding: 0 1.5rem 1.25rem; color: #555; line-height: 1.8; font-size: 0.95rem; }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .step {
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: center;
      text-align: center;
    }

    .sub-cta { background-attachment: scroll; }
  }
</style>
